But, um, thank you.

264
00:14:51,423 --> 00:14:52,789
It's really
good to see you.

265
00:14:59,865 --> 00:15:01,231
Are you going to
take any of those?

266
00:15:01,333 --> 00:15:02,332
You know, I'm going
to think about it

267
00:15:02,433 --> 00:15:04,768
and maybe I'll
be back tomorrow.

268
00:15:04,870 --> 00:15:06,436
I'll look forward to
seeing you there.

269
00:15:18,216 --> 00:15:26,123
[sound of streetcorner
Santa in distance]

270
00:15:29,561 --> 00:15:32,229
I have nothing to wear.

271
00:15:32,330 --> 00:15:33,964
Honey, you look
good in nothing.

272
00:15:34,065 --> 00:15:36,333
I mean whatever you wear;
you're going to look great.

273
00:15:36,434 --> 00:15:37,768
I have nothing
good enough.

274
00:15:37,869 --> 00:15:39,070
Well what about the
lime green pant suit

275
00:15:39,170 --> 00:15:41,037
my mom gave you for
Christmas last year?

276
00:15:41,138 --> 00:15:43,273
Okay, forget that I
even offered that.

277
00:15:43,374 --> 00:15:45,509
Why are we even
going to this?

278
00:15:45,610 --> 00:15:47,378
What? What are you
talking about now?

279
00:15:47,479 --> 00:15:49,947
Well you don't even have to
go to this gallery thing.

280
00:15:50,048 --> 00:15:52,516
We never go anywhere
Gary and this is free.

281
00:15:52,617 --> 00:15:54,384
It's something we
can afford, right?

282
00:16:07,932 --> 00:16:09,032
<i>[woman's voice]</i>
<i>Mrs. K.!</i>

283
00:16:12,037 --> 00:16:13,337
<i>Mrs. K.!</i>

284
00:16:13,438 --> 00:16:14,504
<i>you're going to be late</i>
<i>for your appointment</i>

285
00:16:14,605 --> 00:16:15,973
<i>with Armando!</i>

286
00:16:23,948 --> 00:16:25,449
Oooh, losing my mind!

287
00:16:30,922 --> 00:16:33,423
I hope Santa brings
me a pretty dress.

288
00:16:33,524 --> 00:16:35,292
Yeah, have him
bring me one too.

289
00:16:35,393 --> 00:16:37,027
Hi baby.

290
00:16:37,128 --> 00:16:39,763
Mommy, look, do
you like my Santa?

291
00:16:39,865 --> 00:16:41,665
I do, you did
such a good job!

292
00:16:41,766 --> 00:16:43,334
You didn't even see it.

293
00:16:43,435 --> 00:16:44,635
Oh, I did.

294
00:16:44,736 --> 00:16:46,136
It's as adorable
as you are.

295
00:16:46,237 --> 00:16:48,505
Are you dressed
for an 80s party?

296
00:16:48,606 --> 00:16:49,707
You're funny.

297
00:16:49,808 --> 00:16:52,743
Okay, you girls be
in bed by 10, okay?

298
00:16:52,844 --> 00:16:54,044
Gary?

299
00:16:54,145 --> 00:16:55,545
-Hey, you look terrific.
-Oh, thanks.

300
00:16:55,646 --> 00:16:56,814
Can I have this dance?

301
00:16:56,915 --> 00:16:58,215
Come on, let's go.
We're going to be late.

302
00:16:58,316 --> 00:17:00,417
Eleanor, may I
have this dance?

303
00:17:00,518 --> 00:17:01,852
You have to go,
you'll be late.

304
00:17:01,953 --> 00:17:03,721
I'll dance with you daddy.

305
00:17:03,822 --> 00:17:05,022
You will?

306
00:17:05,123 --> 00:17:06,690
Come on.

307
00:17:06,791 --> 00:17:08,325
Hand please?

308
00:17:08,427 --> 00:17:09,894
Yes.

309
00:17:09,995 --> 00:17:11,962
Dad, you're so weird.

310
00:17:12,063 --> 00:17:13,030
Good night girls.

311
00:17:13,131 --> 00:17:14,331
Let's go.

312
00:17:22,540 --> 00:17:25,108
[shivering]

313
00:17:25,209 --> 00:17:27,911
Your chariot has
arrived Mrs. Ferguson.

314
00:17:28,013 --> 00:17:29,980
I left the pin
in my skirt.

315
00:17:30,081 --> 00:17:32,482
I completely
forgot to sew it!

316
00:17:36,087 --> 00:17:37,321
Oh my god.

317
00:17:37,422 --> 00:17:38,355
Baby, you can't
even see it.

318
00:17:38,456 --> 00:17:39,657
Gary!

319
00:17:39,757 --> 00:17:40,958
There's going to be women
in there whose dresses

320
00:17:41,059 --> 00:17:42,559
cost over $1200.

321
00:17:42,660 --> 00:17:44,428
plus tax.

322
00:17:44,529 --> 00:17:47,198
Mine was at the Goodwill
and it has a pin in it.

323
00:17:47,299 --> 00:17:49,399
You can barely even see
it, I'm telling you.

324
00:17:49,500 --> 00:17:50,601
It looks great.

325
00:17:50,702 --> 00:17:53,002
Oh, Prairie Fauvists.

326
00:17:58,009 --> 00:18:02,946
[music and chatter throughout]

327
00:18:14,926 --> 00:18:18,362
And I replied, sweetie...

328
00:18:18,463 --> 00:18:20,598
...nobody does Aspen
on Christmas day.

329
00:18:20,699 --> 00:18:21,832
Oh Aspen's done.

330
00:18:21,933 --> 00:18:23,634
Everyone goes
to Telluride.

331
00:18:30,241 --> 00:18:32,309
Completely out of date.

332
00:18:33,978 --> 00:18:35,613
Gary, can you not push me?

333
00:18:35,713 --> 00:18:38,615
Do you see anyone else
pushing their wife?

334
00:18:38,717 --> 00:18:40,551
Gary! Paula!

335
00:18:42,721 --> 00:18:44,187
Oh great, the
old flame Janine!

336
00:18:44,289 --> 00:18:45,388
Come on, I like Janine.

337
00:18:45,489 --> 00:18:46,657
Well then, you
talk to her.

338
00:18:48,059 --> 00:18:48,958
Hi guys.

339
00:18:49,060 --> 00:18:50,194
Hi.

340
00:18:50,295 --> 00:18:51,461
Can you believe
this place?

341
00:18:51,562 --> 00:18:53,697
-It's amazing.
-It's pretty great.

342
00:18:55,300 --> 00:18:56,399
How are you Gary?

343
00:18:56,501 --> 00:18:58,702
Not bad. Not bad.

344
00:18:58,803 --> 00:18:59,837
Where's Nick?

345
00:18:59,938 --> 00:19:02,139
Over by the window;

346
00:19:02,240 --> 00:19:03,773
he's the one surrounded
by all the girls -

347
00:19:03,875 --> 00:19:04,842
the same as
high school.

348
00:19:08,079 --> 00:19:09,546
Well, go on and say hi.

349
00:19:09,647 --> 00:19:12,316
We'll just stay here
and discuss painting.

350
00:19:12,417 --> 00:19:13,550
House painting.

351
00:19:14,586 --> 00:19:15,686
Good, have fun.

352
00:19:15,787 --> 00:19:17,087
Thank you.

353
00:19:20,491 --> 00:19:23,093
I bet Nick can't
paint a house.

354
00:19:23,194 --> 00:19:25,696
I bet he doesn't do
copper plumbing either.

355
00:19:28,065 --> 00:19:32,269
[chatter throughout]

356
00:19:42,847 --> 00:19:43,914
Paula.

357
00:19:44,015 --> 00:19:45,082
Nick.

358
00:19:45,183 --> 00:19:46,449
Oh, I didn't even see you.

359
00:19:46,550 --> 00:19:47,584
You made it.

360
00:19:47,686 --> 00:19:49,420
Is Gary here?

361
00:19:49,521 --> 00:19:50,721
Yeah, he's over there.

362
00:19:52,757 --> 00:19:54,491
I want to show
you something;

363
00:19:54,592 --> 00:19:55,725
I'm so glad you came.

364
00:19:57,995 --> 00:19:59,096
Hello.

365
00:19:59,197 --> 00:20:00,798
-Hi sweetie.
-How are you?

366
00:20:00,899 --> 00:20:01,999
Hello, gorgeous.

367
00:20:04,335 --> 00:20:05,735
You look lovely,
both of you.

368
00:20:05,837 --> 00:20:06,970
Great work.

369
00:20:08,506 --> 00:20:11,675
Have to tell you, it really
feels great to be back.

370
00:20:19,817 --> 00:20:21,385
So what do you
think of this?

371
00:20:21,486 --> 00:20:23,987
Very modern.

372
00:20:24,088 --> 00:20:26,523
What is it?

373
00:20:26,624 --> 00:20:27,757
Garbage.

374
00:20:27,858 --> 00:20:30,260
(Laughs)

375
00:20:31,729 --> 00:20:33,062
How you been?

376
00:20:33,164 --> 00:20:36,567
Good.

377
00:20:36,668 --> 00:20:40,670
Gosh it must be so nice
to travel around Europe,

378
00:20:40,771 --> 00:20:42,105
buying art.

379
00:20:42,206 --> 00:20:43,841
Well, I've missed people.

380
00:20:43,942 --> 00:20:46,309
You're surrounded
by people.

381
00:20:46,410 --> 00:20:47,777
Not friends.

382
00:20:52,383 --> 00:20:56,253
I was dating this guy
last year but it fizzled,

383
00:20:56,354 --> 00:20:58,188
he didn't
want kids.

384
00:20:58,289 --> 00:20:59,790
Well, you know what;
you'll find someone

385
00:20:59,891 --> 00:21:01,024
because you're
a good person.

386
00:21:04,862 --> 00:21:08,431
So what are you doing to
keep yourself busy these days?

387
00:21:08,532 --> 00:21:09,800
Life.

388
00:21:09,901 --> 00:21:11,635
I've two girls, so
there is always,

389
00:21:11,736 --> 00:21:13,603
always something.

390
00:21:13,704 --> 00:21:16,773
Yeah.
Kids are great.

391
00:21:16,874 --> 00:21:18,241
I never went
down that road.

392
00:21:18,343 --> 00:21:19,275
No?

393
00:21:19,376 --> 00:21:21,077
Yeah, god,
they're your life.

394
00:21:39,697 --> 00:21:42,399
Would you be interested in
working in a Art Gallery again?

395
00:21:42,500 --> 00:21:44,134
You mean like
working here?

396
00:21:44,235 --> 00:21:46,169
Sh, our secret.

397
00:21:46,270 --> 00:21:47,270
Hi.

398
00:21:47,371 --> 00:21:48,872
Sheila, hi.

399
00:21:48,973 --> 00:21:50,207
Nice to see you again.

400
00:21:50,308 --> 00:21:51,274
You too.

401
00:21:51,375 --> 00:21:54,645
Wow, that's a
fantastic skirt.

402
00:21:54,746 --> 00:21:56,380
Honey, Malcolm and Shanite
would like to talk to you

403
00:21:56,481 --> 00:21:58,448
about the large
piece from Florence.

404
00:21:58,549 --> 00:22:00,283
Mr. and Mrs. Kensington,
photo please?

405
00:22:05,956 --> 00:22:07,791
Good night.
Nice seeing you Paula.

406
00:22:10,561 --> 00:22:11,828
Nice skirt...

407
00:22:14,265 --> 00:22:15,732
I know.

408
00:22:15,833 --> 00:22:17,901
Hey, I'm done.

409
00:22:18,002 --> 00:22:19,135
I'm done.
I'm ready to go.

410
00:22:19,236 --> 00:22:20,371
Okay, hang on.

411
00:22:20,472 --> 00:22:21,538
I'm going to go say
goodbye to Nick.

412
00:22:21,639 --> 00:22:23,073
Why?

413
00:22:23,174 --> 00:22:25,142
Well, because I didn't get
a chance to say hello.

414
00:22:30,147 --> 00:22:31,615
Which piece did you like?

415
00:22:34,952 --> 00:22:36,086
Excuse me, just a second.

416
00:22:38,189 --> 00:22:39,322
You know how
lucky you were?

417
00:22:39,423 --> 00:22:41,125
What?

418
00:22:41,225 --> 00:22:42,526
Dating both of them
in high school?

419
00:22:42,627 --> 00:22:45,128
Yeah.

420
00:22:45,229 --> 00:22:47,831
You ended up with the
right guy though.

421
00:22:47,932 --> 00:22:50,300
I bet Gary's a great dad.

422
00:22:50,401 --> 00:22:52,002
Yeah, he is.

423
00:22:56,106 --> 00:22:59,843
[indistinct chatter]

424
00:23:07,685 --> 00:23:09,953
Did you enjoy
the party?

425
00:23:10,054 --> 00:23:13,523
How's Janine?

426
00:23:13,624 --> 00:23:15,592
Maybe I should have
taken her to Prom.

427
00:23:25,970 --> 00:23:27,304
What are you doing?

428
00:23:27,405 --> 00:23:32,342
[radio playing quietly]

429
00:23:42,220 --> 00:23:44,153
What was dad
drinking last night?

430
00:23:44,254 --> 00:23:45,422
Once we put our
ornaments on it,

431
00:23:45,523 --> 00:23:47,558
the tree will look great.

432
00:23:47,659 --> 00:23:49,859
That's not a tree,
that's a branch.

433
00:23:49,960 --> 00:23:51,961
Admiring our Christmas
branch girls?

434
00:23:55,833 --> 00:23:57,000
All right,
let's go ladies.

435
00:23:57,101 --> 00:23:58,335
Last day of school before
Christmas vacation.

436
00:23:58,436 --> 00:24:00,537
Keep it moving.

437
00:24:00,638 --> 00:24:02,539
Mush. Mush.

438
00:24:02,640 --> 00:24:03,773
Hi girls.

439
00:24:03,874 --> 00:24:05,174
-Hi Reg.
-Hey.

440
00:24:05,276 --> 00:24:06,443
Hey Gary, you ready to go?

441
00:24:06,544 --> 00:24:07,844
<i>I got the lights.</i>

442
00:24:07,946 --> 00:24:09,045
Yeah, do you mind dropping
the girls off a school?

443
00:24:09,146 --> 00:24:09,946
I'll meet you
at the sight.

444
00:24:10,048 --> 00:24:11,081
<i>Yeah, sure.</i>

445
00:24:11,182 --> 00:24:12,216
Come on guys.

446
00:24:12,316 --> 00:24:13,617
Back-packs, back-packs.

447
00:24:13,718 --> 00:24:14,918
Let's go.

448
00:24:15,019 --> 00:24:16,252
Love you daddy.

449
00:24:16,353 --> 00:24:17,354
All right, have
a good day.

450
00:24:17,455 --> 00:24:18,722
-Bye dad.
-Thank you.

451
00:24:21,959 --> 00:24:23,760
How about you
sweetheart?

452
00:24:23,861 --> 00:24:25,361
Me?

453
00:24:25,462 --> 00:24:27,564
Oh, I was booking
a flight to France,

454
00:24:27,665 --> 00:24:28,732
taking in the Louvre,

455
00:24:28,832 --> 00:24:30,701
doing a little holiday
shopping in Paris

456
00:24:30,802 --> 00:24:32,336
and then dinner
at the Ritz.

457
00:24:32,437 --> 00:24:33,436
The usual.

458
00:24:33,538 --> 00:24:35,038
Enjoy the Louvre.

459
00:24:39,510 --> 00:24:40,643
[quietly]
I'm sorry Gary.

460
00:24:48,419 --> 00:24:58,395
[quiet music throughout]

461
00:25:58,422 --> 00:26:03,427
[crying]

462
00:27:25,575 --> 00:27:30,514
[music throughout]

463
00:27:38,256 --> 00:27:40,090
[chuckles]

464
00:27:45,229 --> 00:27:46,696
There you are.

465
00:27:48,532 --> 00:27:50,467
<i>[woman's voice]</i>
<i>Mrs. K., you're</i>
<i>going to be late</i>

466
00:27:50,568 --> 00:27:52,736
<i>for your appointment</i>
<i>with Armando!</i>

467
00:27:57,775 --> 00:28:00,010
<i>Remember lunch at</i>
<i>the club afterward!</i>

468
00:28:07,685 --> 00:28:09,619
Mrs. K...

469
00:28:13,924 --> 00:28:15,492
Mrs. K.!

470
00:28:15,593 --> 00:28:18,027
<i>You're going to be late for</i>
<i>your appointment with Armando!</i>

471
00:28:18,128 --> 00:28:31,441
[Music]

472
00:28:31,542 --> 00:28:43,886
[Music]

473
00:28:43,987 --> 00:28:51,494
[Music]

474
00:28:56,033 --> 00:28:56,966
(Grunts)

475
00:28:57,067 --> 00:28:59,035
Oh!

476
00:29:05,042 --> 00:29:06,042
[gasp!]

477
00:29:06,143 --> 00:29:09,712
Mrs. K., you fall down!

478
00:29:09,813 --> 00:29:12,081
Are you all right?

479
00:29:12,182 --> 00:29:13,083
Yeah.

480
00:29:13,184 --> 00:29:15,751
I think I'm okay.

481
00:29:15,853 --> 00:29:16,987
Let me help you up.

482
00:29:25,897 --> 00:29:27,230
I don't know how
this happened.

483
00:29:27,331 --> 00:29:29,532
Not to worry Mrs. K..

484
00:29:29,633 --> 00:29:31,434
Mrs. K.?

485
00:29:31,536 --> 00:29:34,737
You prefer now I call
you Mrs. Kensington?

486
00:29:34,838 --> 00:29:38,007
<i>[man's voice]</i>
<i>Martina, is Paula up yet?</i>

487
00:29:38,108 --> 00:29:39,009
[whispers]
No!

488
00:29:39,110 --> 00:29:40,977
No, not yet.

489
00:29:41,078 --> 00:29:43,813
Tell her I hired someone to put
<i>up the Christmas lights, okay?</i>

490
00:29:43,914 --> 00:29:45,715
Okay.

491
00:29:48,952 --> 00:29:50,653
Was that Nick
asking for me?

492
00:29:50,754 --> 00:29:52,388
Yes.

493
00:29:52,489 --> 00:29:54,123
Where's Sheila?

494
00:29:54,224 --> 00:29:56,359
Sheila...

495
00:29:56,460 --> 00:29:58,628
At the gallery.

496
00:30:00,164 --> 00:30:04,367
[gasp]

497
00:30:04,468 --> 00:30:06,836
Oh, this is so strange.

498
00:30:06,937 --> 00:30:08,671
I know.

499
00:30:08,773 --> 00:30:11,173
This is a very strange
time for all of us.

500
00:30:11,274 --> 00:30:12,742
Vayamos.

501
00:30:20,117 --> 00:30:21,818
[gasp]

502
00:30:21,919 --> 00:30:25,655
[Music]

503
00:30:25,756 --> 00:30:27,290
[chuckles]

504
00:30:33,064 --> 00:30:35,965
Oh my god,
look at that!

505
00:30:36,500 --> 00:30:40,736
[Unclear]

506
00:30:40,837 --> 00:30:43,139
Oh god, this
is so gorgeous.

507
00:30:43,240 --> 00:30:45,575
Yes, you picked that one
up in Italy this summer.

508
00:30:45,676 --> 00:30:47,210
Very nice.

509
00:30:47,311 --> 00:30:48,845
I picked that up in Italy?

510
00:30:48,946 --> 00:30:52,047
Yes, only the best for
you Mrs. Kensington.

511
00:30:52,149 --> 00:30:53,616
Only the best.

512
00:30:57,221 --> 00:30:58,521
Oh, your hair
appointment...

513
00:30:58,622 --> 00:30:59,689
My hair appointment?

514
00:30:59,790 --> 00:31:01,091
Okay.

515
00:31:01,192 --> 00:31:02,659
One thing.

516
00:31:02,760 --> 00:31:03,659
Yes, yes?

517
00:31:03,760 --> 00:31:05,928
I'm Mrs. Kensington?

518
00:31:06,030 --> 00:31:08,465
Are you feeling all
right Mrs. Kensington?

519
00:31:08,566 --> 00:31:09,933
Why do you keep
calling me that?

520
00:31:11,635 --> 00:31:12,835
Are you're Martina?

521
00:31:12,936 --> 00:31:16,672
Oh please, Mrs. K., it's
been a tough enough day

522
00:31:16,773 --> 00:31:18,574
without you
acting like this.

523
00:31:18,676 --> 00:31:21,478
Did you take too much of
your prescriptions again?

524
00:31:21,579 --> 00:31:23,679
My...? No.

525
00:31:23,780 --> 00:31:25,514
No, good.

526
00:31:25,616 --> 00:31:27,984
There is so much going on;
so much stress already.

527
00:31:28,085 --> 00:31:30,720
You must get going.

528
00:31:30,821 --> 00:31:35,525
This must be a dream,
but it seems so real.

529
00:31:44,635 --> 00:31:47,170
Oh, brunch
at the Club at 11.

530
00:31:47,271 --> 00:31:49,005
Right, brunch at
the Club at 11.

531
00:31:49,106 --> 00:31:50,273
Okay.

532
00:31:50,374 --> 00:31:52,075
