00:44:24,560 --> 00:44:25,427
No wait, wait, wait.

803
00:44:25,529 --> 00:44:27,363
It's my turn.

804
00:44:27,464 --> 00:44:30,131
We're going to 'cheers'.

805
00:44:30,233 --> 00:44:32,701
To new beginnings
at Christmas time.

806
00:44:32,802 --> 00:44:34,503
Did I tell you I feel like
I'm on my first date?

807
00:44:34,604 --> 00:44:37,405
Yes, many times, and your
first date is very late.

808
00:44:37,506 --> 00:44:39,174
Yes, well he was
at the office

809
00:44:39,275 --> 00:44:41,276
meeting with his
new publicist;

810
00:44:41,377 --> 00:44:43,011
they seem to be getting
along very well.

811
00:44:43,112 --> 00:44:45,347
He gets along with women.

812
00:44:47,517 --> 00:44:49,485
I wonder why we
never had kids?

813
00:44:49,586 --> 00:44:51,754
Do you ever wonder
why we never had kids?

814
00:44:51,855 --> 00:44:53,222
No I didn't.

815
00:44:53,323 --> 00:44:54,690
And I'm going to check
the fish, I think,

816
00:44:54,791 --> 00:44:56,325
now it's not so sexy.

817
00:44:56,426 --> 00:44:58,560
Oh wait, what song
should I put on?

818
00:44:58,661 --> 00:45:00,162
What do Nick and I
usually dance to?

819
00:45:00,263 --> 00:45:01,497
He doesn't dance.

820
00:45:01,597 --> 00:45:03,065
-He doesn't?
-No.

821
00:45:03,166 --> 00:45:04,667
Yeah, you know,
he never danced

822
00:45:04,768 --> 00:45:06,402
in high school either.

823
00:45:06,503 --> 00:45:08,637
Now you're seeing
the problems.

824
00:45:08,738 --> 00:45:11,073
[door opens]

825
00:45:11,174 --> 00:45:12,741
Uh-oh.

826
00:45:13,943 --> 00:45:15,077
Dinner ready?

827
00:45:15,178 --> 00:45:18,279
Well hello there stranger!

828
00:45:18,381 --> 00:45:20,248
Turn off that noise.

829
00:45:20,349 --> 00:45:21,250
Well, I thought we'd
do a little samba

830
00:45:21,351 --> 00:45:22,751
before dinner.

831
00:45:22,852 --> 00:45:24,119
What are you
talking about?

832
00:45:24,220 --> 00:45:25,921
I just finished
a long day.

833
00:45:26,022 --> 00:45:27,389
And those damn photos
didn't turn out

834
00:45:27,491 --> 00:45:28,824
for the press packet.

835
00:45:28,925 --> 00:45:31,793
I'm sorry, but you know
samba can be relaxing.

836
00:45:31,895 --> 00:45:33,695
Come on, I'll teach you.

837
00:45:33,796 --> 00:45:34,630
What are you doing?

838
00:45:34,731 --> 00:45:35,798
We don't dance.

839
00:45:35,899 --> 00:45:38,200
Loosen up Nick, come
on, give it a shot.

840
00:45:38,301 --> 00:45:40,436
Come on, it'll be fun.

841
00:45:40,537 --> 00:45:42,204
How much wine
have you had?

842
00:45:42,305 --> 00:45:44,806
Just a couple of glasses.

843
00:45:47,777 --> 00:45:49,278
Why did you stop by today?

844
00:45:49,379 --> 00:45:50,546
Sit down first.

845
00:45:54,317 --> 00:45:57,252
I got you an early
Christmas gift.

846
00:45:57,353 --> 00:45:58,387
We've already
given each other

847
00:45:58,488 --> 00:46:00,289
our Christmas
presents Paula.

848
00:46:00,390 --> 00:46:02,558
Well this is extra.

849
00:46:02,659 --> 00:46:03,692
What is it?

850
00:46:03,793 --> 00:46:06,861
Well, you sir
work way too hard,

851
00:46:08,164 --> 00:46:09,665
and we need a vacation.

852
00:46:14,904 --> 00:46:19,575
I'm starting to feel
very awkward here Paula.

853
00:46:19,675 --> 00:46:22,110
Your dress,
the dancing...

854
00:46:22,212 --> 00:46:23,778
what are you doing?

855
00:46:23,880 --> 00:46:25,214
Paris.

856
00:46:25,314 --> 00:46:28,584
Two tickets; you and moi.

857
00:46:28,685 --> 00:46:32,821
Hotel, spa, museums,
art shows...

858
00:46:32,922 --> 00:46:34,256
We're not going
to Paris Paula.

859
00:46:36,225 --> 00:46:38,660
Okay. It doesn't
have to be Paris.

860
00:46:38,761 --> 00:46:40,495
We could go to Zurich.

861
00:46:40,596 --> 00:46:41,796
What are you
talking about?

862
00:46:41,897 --> 00:46:43,265
What do you mean?

863
00:46:43,366 --> 00:46:45,000
We're getting a divorce.

864
00:46:45,101 --> 00:46:46,401
A divorce?

865
00:46:46,503 --> 00:46:49,437
We're not going anywhere
together, ever again.

866
00:46:49,539 --> 00:46:51,439
That doesn't make sense.

867
00:46:51,540 --> 00:46:53,642
We're having a catered
party on Christmas Eve.

868
00:46:53,743 --> 00:46:55,377
Well, the divorce
is your idea;

869
00:46:55,478 --> 00:46:57,846
come to think of it,
so is the party.

870
00:47:00,850 --> 00:47:02,117
My idea?

871
00:47:02,218 --> 00:47:04,686
Is this some ploy to
re-negotiate the settlement?

872
00:47:04,787 --> 00:47:06,254
Everything is signed.

873
00:47:06,355 --> 00:47:08,456
Paperwork goes through
midnight Christmas Eve.

874
00:47:08,558 --> 00:47:09,657
Midnight?

875
00:47:09,758 --> 00:47:11,926
That's when the sweet
table comes out.

876
00:47:13,229 --> 00:47:16,398
You never could finish
anything could you?

877
00:47:16,499 --> 00:47:18,667
The riding lessons;
cooking classes;

878
00:47:18,768 --> 00:47:21,737
your attempt at art.

879
00:47:21,838 --> 00:47:23,705
Well, I'm finishing
this one for you;

880
00:47:23,807 --> 00:47:26,674
we're over, as is
this conversation.

881
00:47:29,345 --> 00:47:39,288
[soft music]

882
00:47:55,371 --> 00:47:56,972
[sigh]

883
00:48:04,581 --> 00:48:06,515
I need to talk to Nick.

884
00:48:07,817 --> 00:48:09,551
Are you kidding me?

885
00:48:09,652 --> 00:48:10,919
You asked for this
divorce a year ago.

886
00:48:11,021 --> 00:48:13,955
I don't want this now.

887
00:48:14,057 --> 00:48:15,657
Well, it's a little
late for that.

888
00:48:17,260 --> 00:48:19,261
Please, can't we just
try to work this out?

889
00:48:19,362 --> 00:48:21,296
Maybe you should
see Dr. Degolia,

890
00:48:21,397 --> 00:48:22,998
and have him adjust your
prescription again.

891
00:48:25,268 --> 00:48:27,002
No, I don't need a
prescription Nick.

892
00:48:28,872 --> 00:48:30,305
I need you.

893
00:48:30,406 --> 00:48:33,374
After $100,000
in legal fees?

894
00:48:33,475 --> 00:48:36,178
I don't want to have this
conversation with you anymore.

895
00:48:36,279 --> 00:48:37,746
Understand?

896
00:48:37,847 --> 00:48:38,814
Well Nick, maybe
there's something

897
00:48:38,914 --> 00:48:40,382
we haven't tried.

898
00:48:40,483 --> 00:48:41,483
How about counseling.

899
00:48:41,584 --> 00:48:43,518
We spent three years
with Dr. Marson.

900
00:48:43,620 --> 00:48:45,020
But we have everything we
need to make ourselves

901
00:48:45,121 --> 00:48:46,254
perfectly happy.

902
00:48:46,355 --> 00:48:47,689
It doesn't even
make sense.

903
00:48:47,790 --> 00:48:49,458
That's what I
thought a year ago,

904
00:48:49,559 --> 00:48:52,861
but apparently I
made you miserable.

905
00:48:52,962 --> 00:48:57,332
Nick, I don't want us...
this life to just end.

906
00:48:57,434 --> 00:49:00,569
You're unbelievable,
you know that?

907
00:49:00,670 --> 00:49:02,771
You still don't
care about me.

908
00:49:02,872 --> 00:49:03,939
You know I didn't
hear you say, Nick,

909
00:49:04,040 --> 00:49:05,941
I realized I made a
big mistake, or Nick,

910
00:49:06,042 --> 00:49:07,576
I've always loved you,

911
00:49:07,677 --> 00:49:09,544
I'll try to be
a better wife.

912
00:49:09,646 --> 00:49:11,646
All you care about is
having an expense account.

913
00:49:13,850 --> 00:49:15,116
Anyway...

914
00:49:15,218 --> 00:49:17,252
...it doesn't
matter anymore.

915
00:49:17,353 --> 00:49:18,954
The papers are signed.

916
00:49:19,055 --> 00:49:21,056
I'm moving on
with my life,

917
00:49:21,157 --> 00:49:23,758
you should too.

918
00:49:23,859 --> 00:49:25,660
At my age I'd
like the chance

919
00:49:25,761 --> 00:49:27,695
to be with someone
who loves me.

920
00:49:30,400 --> 00:49:32,201
Like Sheila.

921
00:49:33,769 --> 00:49:37,840
Sheila loves me for who I
am, not what I can give.

922
00:49:39,676 --> 00:49:41,576
You know back in
high school Nick,

923
00:49:41,678 --> 00:49:44,245
I dated Gary Ferguson too.

924
00:49:44,347 --> 00:49:46,781
Did you know that?

925
00:49:46,883 --> 00:49:48,950
And I could have gone to the
prom with either one of you,

926
00:49:49,052 --> 00:49:54,489
but in this life
I chose you.

927
00:49:54,590 --> 00:49:55,824
And your point is?

928
00:49:57,026 --> 00:49:58,893
That I chose you!

929
00:50:00,797 --> 00:50:02,464
Life's all about
choices Paula,

930
00:50:04,500 --> 00:50:06,235
every step of the way.

931
00:50:08,171 --> 00:50:09,671
Honey, I just need...

932
00:50:10,940 --> 00:50:12,373
oh...

933
00:50:12,475 --> 00:50:14,643
I'm sorry.

934
00:50:15,945 --> 00:50:16,945
It's okay.

935
00:50:17,046 --> 00:50:18,614
We're done.

936
00:50:37,833 --> 00:50:40,335
Okay, I'm ready to
go home now, okay?

937
00:50:40,436 --> 00:50:42,604
This isn't fun anymore.

938
00:50:42,705 --> 00:50:44,539
I want to wake up
from this dream now.

939
00:51:15,738 --> 00:51:16,605
<i>[Olivia's voice echoes]</i>
<i>Mommy?</i>

940
00:51:16,706 --> 00:51:18,306
<i>Can we keep him?</i>

941
00:51:18,408 --> 00:51:21,242
<i>Mommy, Mommy...Mommy.</i>

942
00:51:21,343 --> 00:51:25,213
<i>Mommy, look what I made.</i>

943
00:51:25,314 --> 00:51:26,815
<i>I love you Mommy.</i>

944
00:51:31,788 --> 00:51:32,854
Oh.

945
00:51:35,024 --> 00:51:36,725
Well, Toto, looks like
we're not getting back

946
00:51:36,826 --> 00:51:39,527
to Kansas.

947
00:51:41,330 --> 00:51:43,865
Can I get you
anything Mrs. K.?

948
00:51:47,369 --> 00:51:49,571
[Music]

949
00:51:58,213 --> 00:51:59,914
Hello? Hello?
Can you hear me?

950
00:52:00,015 --> 00:52:01,350
You lost a sock?

951
00:52:02,051 --> 00:52:03,651
I can't get back.

952
00:52:03,752 --> 00:52:07,856
I can't get back and I've
made a terrible mistake.

953
00:52:07,957 --> 00:52:10,158
Get back?

954
00:52:10,259 --> 00:52:12,594
Where are you going?

955
00:52:12,695 --> 00:52:15,063
I thought this was
where happiness is,

956
00:52:15,164 --> 00:52:17,332
but I need my family back.

957
00:52:20,302 --> 00:52:30,178
[music throughout]

958
00:53:07,082 --> 00:53:13,522
<i>[family laughing and talking]</i>

959
00:53:13,623 --> 00:53:16,992
<i>-You girls...</i>
<i>-I love you.</i>

960
00:53:18,594 --> 00:53:23,598
[music continues]

961
00:54:09,145 --> 00:54:14,816
Mrs. K., you're just
too tired, that's all.

962
00:54:14,917 --> 00:54:17,152
Let's get you to bed.

963
00:54:17,252 --> 00:54:20,088
[Spanish]

964
00:54:20,189 --> 00:54:21,789
You just
need some rest.

965
00:54:21,891 --> 00:54:23,925
[Spanish]

966
00:54:28,064 --> 00:54:30,264
I just want to go home.

967
00:54:35,505 --> 00:54:36,938
You are home.

968
00:54:41,777 --> 00:54:44,212
<i>[girls laughing]</i>

969
00:54:44,313 --> 00:54:46,181
<i>This is so fun.</i>

970
00:54:46,282 --> 00:54:49,450
<i>[voices echo]</i>
<i>Hey Olivia want to come</i>
<i>and play with me and mom?</i>

971
00:54:49,551 --> 00:54:53,188
<i>Hey Mom, can we go up</i>
<i>to the park please?</i>

972
00:54:53,289 --> 00:54:55,423
<i>I love you mom.</i>

973
00:54:55,524 --> 00:54:57,125
<i>I think you're</i>
<i>the coolest.</i>

974
00:55:07,636 --> 00:55:09,303
So how'd you do on your
Global Studies test?

975
00:55:10,806 --> 00:55:12,207
Okay I guess.

976
00:55:12,308 --> 00:55:13,474
The teacher hates me.

977
00:55:13,576 --> 00:55:14,776
She doesn't hate you;

978
00:55:14,877 --> 00:55:16,844
she says such good things
about on parent night.

979
00:55:20,416 --> 00:55:21,616
Potatoes!

980
00:55:21,717 --> 00:55:23,351
Wait a second, what
is she doing here?

981
00:55:23,452 --> 00:55:24,619
Ellie!

982
00:55:24,720 --> 00:55:26,088
How many times have
we talked about this.

983
00:55:26,188 --> 00:55:28,723
No teacher hates you.

984
00:55:28,824 --> 00:55:31,059
Did you just
call her Ellie?

985
00:55:31,160 --> 00:55:32,093
She hates that.

986
00:55:32,194 --> 00:55:33,361
You hate that right?

987
00:55:34,397 --> 00:55:36,431
Miss Becker hates
me; trust me mom.

988
00:55:36,532 --> 00:55:37,932
What?

989
00:55:38,033 --> 00:55:39,667
Did you just call her mom.

990
00:55:39,768 --> 00:55:41,002
Are you kidding me?

991
00:55:46,142 --> 00:55:47,742
Why can't anybody hear me?

992
00:55:47,844 --> 00:55:51,246
Daddy, can we do that
new dance you taught me,

993
00:55:51,347 --> 00:55:52,747
again tonight.

994
00:55:52,848 --> 00:55:55,816
You know,
the Zipperbug?

995
00:55:55,917 --> 00:55:57,686
It's
Jitterbug sweetie,

996
00:55:57,787 --> 00:56:00,455
but daddy always dances
with mommy first.

997
00:56:00,556 --> 00:56:02,023
This can't be happening!

998
00:56:02,124 --> 00:56:05,093
Why can't anybody see me?

999
00:56:05,194 --> 00:56:06,961
Why has she
stolen my family?

1000
00:56:07,062 --> 00:56:08,896
[drill noise]

1001
00:56:08,997 --> 00:56:11,132
Gary?

1002
00:56:11,233 --> 00:56:17,439
[drill noise]

1003
00:56:17,540 --> 00:56:19,274
Gary?

1004
00:56:19,375 --> 00:56:22,410
Lights, lights.

1005
00:56:25,948 --> 00:56:27,282
It's got that funny
sound in it again.

1006
00:56:27,382 --> 00:56:28,883
Really?

1007
00:56:28,985 --> 00:56:30,919
Yeah.

1008
00:56:31,020 --> 00:56:32,621
I bought it used.

1009
00:56:32,722 --> 00:56:35,022
Janine will kill me if I
have to buy another one.

1010
00:56:35,124 --> 00:56:38,626
So, what does Janine think
about you working here?

1011
00:56:38,727 --> 00:56:40,628
We need the money.

1012
00:56:40,729 --> 00:56:42,163
Yeah.

1013
00:56:42,264 --> 00:56:45,166
Yeah.

1014
00:56:45,267 --> 00:56:47,001
Janine's a great lady.

1015
00:57:04,220 --> 00:57:06,187
[clears throat]
Hi Reg.

1016
00:57:11,060 --> 00:57:12,727
How you doing Gary?

1017
00:57:12,828 --> 00:57:15,330
Oh, good, good.

1018
00:57:15,431 --> 00:57:19,700
You'll tell me if the
reindeer are all crooked.

1019
00:57:19,802 --> 00:57:21,502
I don't want to give you
any crooked reindeer.

1020
00:57:21,603 --> 00:57:24,940
Santa's very meticulous
about the reindeer.

1021
00:57:25,040 --> 00:57:26,474
No, it looks great.

1022
00:57:26,575 --> 00:57:27,942
I mean, I think the middle
one looks like it's ready

1023
00:57:28,044 --> 00:57:29,344
for takeoff, but...

1024
00:57:29,445 --> 00:57:31,045
Is that Dasher or Donner,

1025
00:57:31,146 --> 00:57:32,747
because usually I have
trouble with Blitzen.

1026
00:57:32,848 --> 00:57:35,383
You know what, I'll just
straighten the reindeer.

1027
00:57:35,484 --> 00:57:36,517
How come you put up
all these lights

1028
00:57:36,618 --> 00:57:38,152
at Nick's house
and not ours?

1029
00:57:40,155 --> 00:57:41,089
At ours?

1030
00:57:41,190 --> 00:57:42,623
At yours.

1031
00:57:42,725 --> 00:57:43,891
At your house.

1032
00:57:43,992 --> 00:57:47,828
Well, one I get paid I'll
put my lights up at home.

1033
00:57:47,930 --> 00:57:50,031
I got a little trouble
with the drill right now.

1034
00:57:50,132 --> 00:57:52,434
Reg can't tell if it's the
motor or the cable, so...

1035
00:57:52,535 --> 00:57:53,768
Really?

1036
00:57:53,869 --> 00:57:55,202
I'm sorry to hear that,

1037
00:57:55,304 --> 00:57:56,605
but maybe it's a really
good time to take a break.

1038
00:57:56,705 --> 00:57:57,906
And go grab some lunch?

1039
00:58:00,242 --> 00:58:01,476
Lunch?

1040
00:58:01,577 --> 00:58:03,578
Yeah, I'm going
down to the club.

1041
00:58:03,679 --> 00:58:06,914
It is so festive there;
you would love it.

1042
00:58:07,884 --> 00:58:11,786
Actually Janine packed
me a club sandwich,

1043
00:58:11,887 --> 00:58:16,124
so that's about the only
club I'm gonna taste today.

1044
00:58:16,225 --> 00:58:17,458
Yeah, but I thought maybe it
could be a really good time

1045
00:58:17,559 --> 00:58:19,059
for us to do
some catching up.

1046
00:58:21,196 --> 00:58:22,497
It's my treat.

1047
00:58:22,598 --> 00:58:24,299
Nick's treat.

1048
00:58:24,400 --> 00:58:26,333
Yeah, he's doing
pretty well,

1049
00:58:26,434 --> 00:58:31,205
but I think I'm
gonna hang with Reg.

1050
00:58:34,209 --> 00:58:36,811
Gary, don't you remember
when you used to pick me up

1051
00:58:36,912 --> 00:58:40,482
from work and we'd go
have lunch at the Bluffs?

1052
00:58:43,685 --> 00:58:46,721
Yeah I do, I do
remember that.

1053
00:58:46,822 --> 00:58:48,456
That was a long time ago.

1054
00:58:48,557 --> 00:58:50,724
I'm just going to Armando's
and to do a little shopping.

1055
00:58:50,826 --> 00:58:52,459
I could be back and pick
you up around noon.

1056
00:58:52,561 --> 00:58:56,163
Uh, noon.

1057
00:58:56,264 --> 00:58:57,265
I've got a lot
of work to do;

1058
00:58:59,201 --> 00:59:00,334
a lot of work to do,

1059
00:59:00,436 --> 00:59:02,436
but thank you.

1060
00:59:02,538 --> 00:59:03,737
Janine made me
that sandwich,

